WEBVTT

00:02.134 --> 00:05.105
[jazz music]

00:05.137 --> 00:12.178
♪ ♪

00:20.687 --> 00:22.355
- From
the Penn & Teller Theater

00:22.388 --> 00:24.423
at the Rio Hotel Las Vegas,

00:24.457 --> 00:28.827
here's our host,
Alyson Hannigan!

00:28.861 --> 00:35.902
♪ ♪

00:40.372 --> 00:41.941
- Welcome
to a brand-new episode

00:41.975 --> 00:43.243
of "Fool Us."

00:43.276 --> 00:45.878
I can't wait for tonight's acts
to get their shot

00:45.911 --> 00:47.280
at fooling Penn and Teller.

00:47.313 --> 00:50.082
And since I'm the host
of the show, I'm not waiting.

00:50.115 --> 00:52.484
Let's get this party started
and bring out

00:52.518 --> 00:55.021
our main men in magic,
Penn and Teller.

00:55.054 --> 01:02.094
♪ ♪

01:08.700 --> 01:11.037
The prize
is the "Fool Us" trophy

01:11.070 --> 01:12.871
and a spot performing in Penn

01:12.906 --> 01:14.974
and Teller's amazing
magic show.

01:15.007 --> 01:18.811
The winner could be
our first magician right here.

01:18.844 --> 01:21.046
[twangy music]

01:21.081 --> 01:23.115
- In the village
where I am from,

01:23.149 --> 01:25.784
girls were not given
the same opportunities as boys.

01:27.519 --> 01:29.722
They were not even
allowed an education.

01:29.756 --> 01:31.424
Even when I became
a performer,

01:31.457 --> 01:33.960
I felt like I had
to prove myself

01:33.992 --> 01:38.131
because, in Indian society,
magic is really male dominated.

01:38.831 --> 01:40.667
I did bigger
and bigger effects

01:40.700 --> 01:42.502
to make my name

01:42.534 --> 01:45.237
until I did
the biggest escape of all.

01:45.271 --> 01:48.974
It was a flame escape
with a crane that dangled me

01:49.008 --> 01:51.610
in a box 100 feet in the air

01:51.644 --> 01:54.180
and then dropped me
into a fire

01:54.213 --> 01:57.317
so big, it could be seen
for miles.

01:58.084 --> 01:59.519
I know this was crazy,

01:59.551 --> 02:01.521
but no one has ever done
it again

02:01.554 --> 02:03.156
in quite the same way.

02:04.656 --> 02:06.959
These days, I put more
of myself into magic

02:06.992 --> 02:11.097
by including my other loves--
music and dance.

02:11.131 --> 02:14.634
I'm known enough now that when
we go back to the village,

02:14.667 --> 02:17.971
they tell us
how proud they are of me.

02:18.003 --> 02:21.174
I want other girls
to see me on "Fool Us"

02:21.206 --> 02:23.742
and know they can be
what they want to be.

02:23.776 --> 02:26.079
I chose my own destiny.

02:31.783 --> 02:36.322
- Joining us from India,
give it up for Anchal.

02:36.355 --> 02:38.991
[cheers and applause]

02:39.025 --> 02:41.995
[dramatic music]

02:42.027 --> 02:49.067
♪ ♪

03:02.981 --> 03:05.284
- Penn, Teller, Alyson,

03:05.318 --> 03:09.756
and my audience from all over
the world, namaste from India.

03:09.788 --> 03:13.293
Firstly, I would like to say
thank you for having me here.

03:13.325 --> 03:16.396
It is indeed an honor
and pleasure for me

03:16.429 --> 03:18.564
to perform on this stage.

03:18.598 --> 03:21.067
Well, today I'm going
to show you something

03:21.099 --> 03:23.468
that you have
probably seen before.

03:23.502 --> 03:25.972
However, I'm going to
present it to you

03:26.004 --> 03:28.341
with some of my twist.

03:28.373 --> 03:30.409
So we have Hammond with us.

03:30.443 --> 03:32.245
Would you please come
and join me on stage?

03:34.180 --> 03:35.914
Thank you.
So Hammond, would you please

03:35.949 --> 03:38.685
verify to our audience
that we have not set this up?

03:38.718 --> 03:40.954
- We have not set this up.
- All right.

03:40.986 --> 03:45.123
So I have
a few lipsticks with me.

03:45.158 --> 03:48.561
A lot of different colors
like pink, red,

03:48.594 --> 03:50.829
purple, maroon.
Please pick one.

03:52.865 --> 03:54.901
- That's a pink color.
- That's a good choice.

03:54.933 --> 03:56.269
- [Inaudible]
- Now, I would like you

03:56.301 --> 03:59.405
to make a mark on Riya's cheek.

04:06.645 --> 04:09.115
All right.
Now I have

04:09.147 --> 04:11.016
a few markers with me,

04:11.050 --> 04:14.554
all different colors.
Please pick any two.

04:14.586 --> 04:18.925
♪ ♪

04:18.957 --> 04:20.627
All right.
Red and black.

04:20.660 --> 04:22.327
That's a good choice.

04:22.362 --> 04:25.430
Now, I would like you
to put your initials

04:25.464 --> 04:26.832
on any one of her palms.

04:26.865 --> 04:33.906
♪ ♪

04:36.341 --> 04:38.845
That's nice.
Now, use another marker

04:38.877 --> 04:42.314
and put your credit card number
on her other palm.

04:42.348 --> 04:44.216
- Is that a monkey?

04:44.250 --> 04:45.550
- Credit card number?

04:45.584 --> 04:46.653
- I'm just joking.

04:46.685 --> 04:49.254
You can make
any design or any shape.

04:49.288 --> 04:50.822
Whatever you want.

04:50.856 --> 04:57.896
♪ ♪

04:58.497 --> 05:00.899
Perfect.
Can I have this?

05:00.932 --> 05:02.267
Thank you so much.

05:02.302 --> 05:04.403
So now please
take your seats

05:04.437 --> 05:06.238
and enjoy the act.

05:06.271 --> 05:09.274
And so now we have Riya

05:09.309 --> 05:12.312
with two unique marks
on her palms

05:12.345 --> 05:15.747
and one on her cheek.

05:15.781 --> 05:18.550
All right, folks.
Let's do this.

05:18.584 --> 05:21.553
[upbeat music]

05:21.586 --> 05:28.627
♪ ♪

05:40.872 --> 05:45.478
So Penn, Teller, please keep
your eyes on the marks.

05:45.511 --> 05:52.552
♪ ♪

06:27.286 --> 06:29.654
So Hammond, could you please
come back to the stage?

06:29.689 --> 06:32.225
Are these the marks
made by you?

06:32.257 --> 06:33.925
Verify them.

06:33.959 --> 06:35.762
- Right.
- Right.

06:35.795 --> 06:39.531
Wait a minute.
This is, too?

06:40.600 --> 06:41.968
- Right.

06:42.000 --> 06:44.903
- This is Riya face, right?
- Right.

06:44.937 --> 06:47.240
- Hey, be careful.

06:47.273 --> 06:54.312
♪ ♪

07:20.238 --> 07:22.240
[cheers and applause]

07:22.274 --> 07:25.211
♪ ♪

07:28.613 --> 07:32.518
- Anchal!

07:32.552 --> 07:34.920
- Hi.
Namaste.

07:34.954 --> 07:38.223
- That was so good
and so beautiful.

07:38.257 --> 07:40.725
And there were
monkeys in there.

07:42.728 --> 07:44.430
- There were, as our audience.

07:45.764 --> 07:47.899
- So how long have
you been in magic?

07:48.600 --> 07:51.336
- So it's almost 23 years.
- Wow.

07:52.004 --> 07:55.707
- I have done more
than 12,500 stage shows.

07:55.740 --> 07:58.978
- That sounds like
it could be a world record.

07:59.011 --> 08:01.547
- Yeah, it could be.
It could be.

08:02.081 --> 08:04.516
- Is your family in magic also?

08:04.550 --> 08:08.019
- My parents are engineer
by profession.

08:08.053 --> 08:09.322
They both are engineers,

08:09.355 --> 08:13.425
but magic was
my father's hobby.

08:13.459 --> 08:18.297
So to build my career,
my parents left their job.

08:18.331 --> 08:21.233
My parents, my brother--they
all support me in the shows.

08:21.266 --> 08:23.903
- Aww.
Okay, Anchal.

08:23.935 --> 08:25.370
Let's find out if your magic

08:25.403 --> 08:27.973
was powerful enough
to fool Penn and Teller.

08:29.375 --> 08:31.978
- Hey, Anchal.
Boy, what a great act.

08:32.010 --> 08:33.479
What a great act.

08:33.513 --> 08:38.183
And you did perhaps
the biggest miracle possible.

08:38.216 --> 08:41.620
You had a monkey
run across the screen,

08:41.653 --> 08:44.056
and we still watched
the magic trick.

08:45.057 --> 08:46.625
We were able
to keep it together

08:46.658 --> 08:48.293
even when there was a monkey

08:48.326 --> 08:51.663
'cause we have never had
a monkey run across our stage.

08:51.697 --> 08:54.500
And you just kept going.
It's just so great.

08:54.533 --> 08:59.238
And what this is called
is a stretcher illusion,

08:59.272 --> 09:00.673
but you did...
- Yes.

09:00.706 --> 09:02.542
- A version with provers
in it.

09:02.575 --> 09:05.845
The signing the hands
and the face,

09:05.878 --> 09:08.581
putting those provers in
make it a much better trick,

09:08.614 --> 09:11.283
but also, I believe
the stretcher illusion

09:11.317 --> 09:12.751
is what we would consider

09:12.784 --> 09:16.022
kind of
a--kind of a Vegas illusion,

09:16.054 --> 09:20.326
and you make it totally Indian.
It's just so beautiful.

09:20.359 --> 09:25.298
And it's so wonderful
to have somebody from India on,

09:25.331 --> 09:28.301
so far away.
And also, I don't think

09:28.333 --> 09:30.001
there are many women
Indian magicians.

09:30.036 --> 09:31.336
Are there?

09:31.370 --> 09:32.837
- No, they are not so many.

09:32.871 --> 09:34.874
There are very few
as compared to boys.

09:34.907 --> 09:37.976
- We're very honored that
you came on our show,

09:38.009 --> 09:39.345
and so nice to see you.

09:39.378 --> 09:42.181
But it is a stretcher illusion

09:42.213 --> 09:44.250
that we are familiar with,

09:44.283 --> 09:46.918
but we love all the stuff
you did to it,

09:46.952 --> 09:50.690
the way you made it
so complicated, and a monkey.

09:52.991 --> 09:55.360
- Anchal, do they know
how you did your trick?

09:55.394 --> 09:57.330
- Of course.
They are legends.

09:57.996 --> 10:00.131
But to be on the show
in front of them,

10:00.166 --> 10:02.234
it's the greatest honor
for me.

10:02.268 --> 10:03.869
Thank you so much
for having me.

10:03.903 --> 10:04.870
Thank you.
- Thank you.

10:04.903 --> 10:06.072
So wonderful
to have you on.

10:06.105 --> 10:09.107
Thank you.
- Thank you so much, Anchal.

10:09.140 --> 10:12.177
[cheers and applause]

10:14.580 --> 10:16.649
Penn and Teller
will take on more magicians

10:16.682 --> 10:18.750
and then perform
a trick of their own.

10:18.783 --> 10:20.852
Lots more "Fool Us" coming up.

10:20.885 --> 10:23.855
[jazz music]

10:23.889 --> 10:25.157
♪ ♪

10:27.860 --> 10:30.895
[jazz music]

10:32.965 --> 10:34.734
- We're back,
and Penn and Teller

10:34.767 --> 10:37.235
are ready to take
another swing at trick.

10:37.269 --> 10:38.971
Let's see
who's bringing the heat.

10:41.807 --> 10:44.176
- I always liked magic,
but I never really got into it

10:44.210 --> 10:47.278
until I was, like, about 40.
And I'm recently retired.

10:47.312 --> 10:48.713
I've dropped out
of the real world.

10:48.748 --> 10:50.115
That's what I tell people.

10:50.149 --> 10:52.784
The only thing that matters
to me is magic.

10:52.817 --> 10:54.419
I love performing.

10:54.452 --> 10:57.355
I just love to see people's
faces when I blow their minds.

10:57.389 --> 11:00.225
I'm probably having
as much fun as they are.

11:00.259 --> 11:03.729
When I go out to perform,
I might have 40 tricks on me,

11:03.763 --> 11:07.133
cards and wallets,
and all kinds of things.

11:07.166 --> 11:08.868
I get a lot of repeat people,
and they're like,

11:08.900 --> 11:10.436
"You got
something new this week?"

11:10.469 --> 11:12.370
And I'm like,
"I always have something new."

11:12.404 --> 11:15.206
This past year, I've been
doing a ton of magic online.

11:15.240 --> 11:19.644
A new trick every day turned
into my 100-day magic project.

11:19.678 --> 11:23.115
I've done 151 tricks.
The trick I'm doing tonight

11:23.149 --> 11:25.518
involves having
some skin in the game.

11:25.551 --> 11:28.053
Not necessarily my skin,
but somebody's skin.

11:28.086 --> 11:29.422
We'll see what happens.

11:30.655 --> 11:33.692
[cheers and applause]

11:34.626 --> 11:38.998
- Here to perform something
extraordinary is Mark Doetsch.

11:42.835 --> 11:46.004
- There's something special
about the letter X.

11:46.938 --> 11:52.043
Generation X, X marks the spot,
"X-Files," "X-Men."

11:53.078 --> 11:57.383
There's no more powerful symbol
than X, and I can prove it.

11:58.116 --> 11:59.884
Alyson, can you give me a hand?

11:59.918 --> 12:01.653
- Sure.

12:01.687 --> 12:03.522
[mysterious orchestral music]

12:03.556 --> 12:05.157
- I mean, literally,
give me a hand.

12:05.191 --> 12:07.692
- Oh.
- Prepare to experience

12:07.726 --> 12:09.427
the power of the X.

12:09.461 --> 12:12.798
- [laughs] Okay.
- Feel the power.

12:12.831 --> 12:15.701
The experiment begins.

12:15.735 --> 12:18.803
And what's
a magical science experiment

12:18.837 --> 12:20.538
without a little fire?

12:20.572 --> 12:27.613
♪ ♪

12:28.813 --> 12:32.751
If I place my hand
over the flame,

12:32.784 --> 12:35.354
ouch, it hurts.

12:35.386 --> 12:39.457
But if I add to my palm
two deceptively simple lines,

12:39.491 --> 12:41.726
one over the other...

12:41.760 --> 12:45.798
♪ ♪

12:45.831 --> 12:47.633
- X.

12:49.902 --> 12:55.474
- It increases my magical
powers exponentially.

12:55.508 --> 12:56.642
I can't explain this.

12:56.674 --> 13:01.046
♪ ♪

13:01.080 --> 13:03.948
And now, I feel no pain.

13:07.086 --> 13:08.821
- I feel like
I should stop you.

13:08.854 --> 13:10.155
- Alyson, it's your turn.

13:10.188 --> 13:11.423
- Oh.
- Are you ready?

13:11.456 --> 13:12.591
- Not really.

13:12.625 --> 13:14.293
- Don't worry.
I'll give you the power.

13:14.326 --> 13:16.995
All we have to do
is bump fists three times.

13:17.028 --> 13:20.466
One, two, three.
Don't move.

13:20.499 --> 13:22.500
Did you feel anything?

13:22.534 --> 13:23.635
If we take a look,

13:23.668 --> 13:25.804
the X has left my hand

13:25.837 --> 13:28.908
and traveled into yours.

13:28.941 --> 13:30.009
[audience exclaims]

13:30.042 --> 13:31.576
- Whoa!

13:31.610 --> 13:34.613
- Wow.
- Alyson...

13:34.647 --> 13:36.749
- Yes.
- You now have the X-factor.

13:38.017 --> 13:40.786
Let's test your new superpowers
by putting your hand

13:40.820 --> 13:42.822
into the fire.
Sound good?

13:42.855 --> 13:45.090
- No, I was taught
not play with fire.

13:45.124 --> 13:47.192
- Bring your--bring the X down
over the flame

13:47.225 --> 13:48.193
all the way down

13:48.226 --> 13:49.495
as close as you can go.

13:49.528 --> 13:52.565
All the way down.

13:52.597 --> 13:54.365
Wow.

13:54.399 --> 13:57.536
Now, Alyson,
under normal circumstances,

13:57.570 --> 13:58.671
I wouldn't be able to hold
your hand

13:58.703 --> 13:59.938
over a flame like this.

13:59.971 --> 14:01.072
- I mean, I hope not.

14:01.105 --> 14:02.942
- But you are now X woman.

14:02.975 --> 14:04.576
- Hey!
Thank you.

14:04.610 --> 14:05.778
- All right.

14:05.811 --> 14:07.245
But let's prove this
another way.

14:07.278 --> 14:09.315
- Okay.
- Let's try your unmarked hand.

14:09.347 --> 14:10.783
- Oh.
- The one without the X.

14:10.816 --> 14:12.650
- Are you trying to burn me?
- Well, let's see how close

14:12.684 --> 14:14.119
you can get to the fire
with that one.

14:14.153 --> 14:15.453
- Okay.

14:15.486 --> 14:17.322
- Bring it down as close
as you can go.

14:18.756 --> 14:20.592
- Yeah, it's hot.
- That's hot.

14:20.625 --> 14:22.327
Just as I expected.

14:23.828 --> 14:27.799
But if you have any doubts,
Alyson, try the X hand again.

14:27.832 --> 14:30.235
Bring that down over the flame
all the way down.

14:31.269 --> 14:33.138
- It's scary.
- You can do it.

14:33.172 --> 14:35.474
- Okay.
- You have the X power, Alyson.

14:35.506 --> 14:37.209
- Yeah. All right.
- That's crazy.

14:37.243 --> 14:40.245
- Yeah. Wow.
- Isn't that something?

14:40.278 --> 14:41.880
- Amazing.
- I know. Alyson...

14:41.913 --> 14:43.249
- Weird.

14:43.282 --> 14:45.084
- You may be thinking
the X isn't so special.

14:45.116 --> 14:48.386
Maybe any letter will work.
Let's try its cousin, the Y.

14:49.020 --> 14:52.157
That's the letter
for questioners and skeptics.

14:53.692 --> 14:55.427
Let me have your unmarked hand.
- Oh, man.

14:55.461 --> 14:58.230
I feel like
I'm gonna get burned, guys.

14:58.264 --> 15:00.432
♪ ♪

15:00.466 --> 15:02.934
Right.
- No quite an X,

15:02.967 --> 15:05.703
but it's close.
Let's see what it can do.

15:05.738 --> 15:08.774
Bring the Y down
over the flame.

15:08.807 --> 15:11.243
- It's already hot.
- It's too hot?

15:11.277 --> 15:12.477
- Yeah.
- You can't do it?

15:12.510 --> 15:15.447
- No.
- Only the hand with the X

15:15.480 --> 15:17.917
has the power to do this.

15:17.950 --> 15:21.320
But if we add one line,

15:21.352 --> 15:25.356
one little line to that Y,

15:25.390 --> 15:27.091
it now becomes an X.

15:27.927 --> 15:31.797
Now bring your hand down over
the flame, all the way down.

15:31.830 --> 15:33.932
You can even touch the glass.

15:33.966 --> 15:36.634
- What?

15:36.668 --> 15:38.102
- Alyson.
- Yeah.

15:38.136 --> 15:40.105
- You can leave it there
as long as you like.

15:40.139 --> 15:41.974
- I mean, I don't
really like this.

15:43.942 --> 15:45.878
- You have just witnessed
Alyson

15:45.911 --> 15:48.047
defying expectations

15:48.080 --> 15:50.849
with the magical power
of the X.

15:52.717 --> 15:54.953
- Mark Doetsch.

15:54.986 --> 15:56.922
Wow. All right.

15:56.956 --> 15:59.124
So you clearly weren't taught,
"Don't play with fire."

15:59.158 --> 16:01.493
- I guess not.
I guess not.

16:01.527 --> 16:04.062
- It's very, very intriguing.

16:04.096 --> 16:05.764
I don't know how you did that.
- Thank you.

16:05.798 --> 16:07.799
- So if it was up to me,
you'd get the trophy.

16:07.832 --> 16:09.534
- Oh, so I fooled you?
- Yeah.

16:09.567 --> 16:11.235
- But that's not too hard
to do, though.

16:11.269 --> 16:12.804
- Doesn't matter, right?
- Sorry.

16:12.837 --> 16:13.905
- That's all right.

16:13.938 --> 16:15.941
- Who do you love
to perform for most?

16:15.975 --> 16:19.144
- Well, I love
doing close-up magic,

16:19.177 --> 16:21.245
table with table,
that kind of thing.

16:21.279 --> 16:23.916
- And does magic change
the way you see the world?

16:25.451 --> 16:26.585
- Probably.

16:26.618 --> 16:28.653
It puts a smile
on my face,

16:28.687 --> 16:32.024
and pretty much everyone
I come into contact with,

16:32.057 --> 16:33.392
which I love.

16:33.424 --> 16:35.126
- Yeah.
All right.

16:35.894 --> 16:38.463
Shall we see if the power
of X will get you a trophy?

16:38.496 --> 16:40.231
- All right.

16:40.264 --> 16:41.933
- Hey, Mark.
- Hey.

16:41.966 --> 16:45.269
- My compliments to you,
and they are many,

16:45.303 --> 16:47.306
but they all come down
to one simple thing.

16:47.338 --> 16:50.341
I like the lack of showbiz.

16:50.375 --> 16:54.013
I like the fact that you just
came out and presented a trick.

16:54.046 --> 16:55.246
- Thank you.
- And, you know,

16:55.279 --> 16:57.548
people are watching
the show for that.

16:57.582 --> 16:59.784
And a lot of times
they get a lot

16:59.817 --> 17:01.886
of razzle-dazzle and sparkle,

17:01.919 --> 17:03.589
and you just came out and said,

17:03.621 --> 17:06.125
"Here's a really hard trick."

17:06.157 --> 17:07.692
I mean, we knew
the ashes thing.

17:07.726 --> 17:10.128
You know, we knew you getting
the X on the palm,

